						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone near the Basavaṇṇa temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Indra III—A.D. 915-16.</p>						

						<p>This inscription refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Indara Ballaha</hi> <hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> Indra III and is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 837, Yuva,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 915-16.</hi> Further details of the date are not given. It mentions a certain <hi rend="bold">Dhōra</hi> as governing the <hi rend="bold">Banavāsi-nāḍu</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Āychaṇṇa</hi> as the <hi rend="italic">nāḻgāvuṇḍa</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Kuḍuvaṇṇagaṇḍa Seventy</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Iṭṭage Thirty.</hi> It is badly damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
